HEADWORD: Crookedness
<hw>Crook"ed*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The condition or quality of
being crooked; hence, deformity of body or of mind; deviation from moral
rectitude; perverseness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crooken</ent>⟦br⟧
